<BaseLayout
  title="Why Sync Licensing Matters | How Much Music"
  description="How film, TV, ads, and trailers can reshape music earnings."
  type="article"
>
  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow">Explainer</p>
    <h1>Why sync licensing matters</h1>
    <p>
      A sync placement can create a sharp revenue spike and also restart a song's streaming life.
      The immediate fee matters, but the secondary discovery effect often matters just as much.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why some songs sync well</h2>
    <ul class="meta-list">
      <li>Immediate emotional clarity.</li>
      <li>Strong cultural recognition.</li>
      <li>Flexible use in film, TV, trailers, games, or short-form video.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why it changes long-term earnings</h2>
    <p>
      Sync use can push an older recording back into playlists, charts, social media edits, and
      catalog discovery. That is why a single placement can keep paying long after the fee clears.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
